After you have created a Landscape, you can now do any of the following to it:

* Modify its shape in [Sculpt](Engine/Landscape\Editing\SculptMode) mode.
* Modify its appearance in [Paint](Engine/Landscape\Editing\PaintMode) mode.
* Change the size, shape, and type of [Brush](Engine/Landscape\Editing\Brushes) you use to modify the Landscape's shape and appearance.
* Modify the size and shape of its components in [Manage](Engine/Landscape\Editing\ManageMode) mode.
* Copy, paste, import, and export parts of the Landscape's heightmap with [Landscape Gizmos](Engine/Landscape\Editing\Gizmos).
* Modify the Landscape's [Material](Engine/Landscape\Materials).
* Create [Splines](Engine/Landscape\Editing\Splines) for any linear features you want to use in your Landscape.
* Create [holes](Engine/Landscape\Materials) in your Landscape for features such as caves.

For information about creating Landscapes, see [](Engine/Landscape\Creation).

For a quick reference guide to the various Landscape tool modes and options, see [](Engine/Landscape/UI).

For examples of the Landscape tool in action, see the [](Resources\ContentExamples\Landscapes).

[REGION:tip]
The Landscape Tools also work in the VR Editor. For the controls for using Landscape in VR, see the [](Engine/Editor/VR/Controls).
[/REGION]


